In other words, `from api.utils import must_not_be_blank` is executed while `api.utils` is already being imported. At that point, `api.utils` is half-done and importing something from it may fail. And it does fail.

That is called a circular import. You should reorganize the code so that you don&#39;t have circular imports, i.e. if `A` imports `B` and `B` imports `C`, then `C` should not import `A` or `B`.

